==Old English==
===Etymology===
Cognate with Old High German [[durs]] ‘demon’, Old Norse [[ðurs]] ‘giant’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /θyrs/

===Noun===
'''þyrs''' ''m''
# a [[monster]], a [[demon]], a [[giant]]
#:''Þyrs sceal on fenne gewunian ana innan lande'': the monster must live in the fen, alone in its land.  (''Maxims II'')

